    <td><strong>Description:</strong></td>
    <td>Use the <code>chrome.bluetooth</code> module
    to connect to a Bluetooth device.
    For example,
    the <a href="https://github.com/GoogleChrome/chrome-app-samples/tree/master/zephyr_hxm">zephyr_hxm sample</a>
    uses the Bluetooth API to fetch heart rate data
    from a Zephyr HXM device (a very simple heart rate monitor driver).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Availability:</strong></td>
    <td>Google Chrome Dev Channel Only</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Permissions:</strong></td>
    <td><code>"bluetooth"</code></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
